    <item>
      <title>My Article Name</title>
      <link>https://pauloborba.github.io/post/my-article-name/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 08 Jan 2019 20:14:56 -0300</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://pauloborba.github.io/post/my-article-name/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I do not like rankings. &lt;a href=&#34;http://cacm.acm.org/magazines/2016/9/206263-academic-rankings-considered-harmful/fulltext#.V735Hbwc1Ck.twitter&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Academic Rankings Considered Harmful!&lt;/a&gt;  clearly summarises ideas I believe in: &amp;ldquo;An academic decision is typically a multi-objective optimization problem, in which the objective function is highly personal. A unidimensional ranking provides a seductively easy objective function to optimize. Yet such decision making ignores the complex interplay between individual preferences and programs&amp;rsquo; unique patterns of strengths and weaknesses. Decision making by ranking is decision making by lazy minds, I believe&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I especially like its summary: &amp;ldquo;Academic rankings are harmful, I believe. We have a responsibility to better inform the public, by ceasing to play the ranking games and by providing the public with relevant information&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
